    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>Disciplined and battle-hardened, the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] are an elite legion in [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' army. They spearheaded the conquest of the [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url]  - finding themselves always outnumbered, but never outclassed. Led by the steadfast and dutiful [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url], whom they follow with obsessive devotion, they are committed to imposing their interpretation of order upon the relative lawlessness of the Tiers.

The legion only tolerates Northerners in their ranks, priding themselves on their high standards and cultural purity. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>The last of the great Northern Generals to stand against the Overlord in ages past, Archon [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] now serves [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] as supreme commander of the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] legion, and is charged with conquering the Tiers.

[url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] shares a powerful bond with the soldiers under his command, and regards each of them as family. The death of a soldier at enemy hands represents a grievous loss to the old General, who bears the burden of his love with mournful stoicism. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] is little more than a gang of thugs and their captive slaves. Rather than organize under commissioned officers, the Chorus follow a hierarchy seemingly ruled by whoever has the bravado to command and defend their position. At the head of this chaotic pecking order, the Archon of Secrets, better known as [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url], treats the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] as his personal army. 

The [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] often suffers tremendous losses after battle, only to swell in the aftermath when captured enemies and collateral prisoners are given the cruel opportunity to join or die. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>Known in his official capacity as the Archon of Secrets, [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] is equal parts genius and madman. Rumors abound that he can steal the minds of others, though few (if any) are alive to confirm as much. The subjects of his interrogation are never heard from again, and the Archon is able to recall the memories of his victims with startling accuracy.

He is the inconsistent leader of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] - vacillating between commanding from the vanguard and directing his armies in absentia. Despite his strange methods, no one doubts that [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url] is an accomplished strategist, even suggesting that his madness stems from thinking hundreds, perhaps thousands of steps ahead of his enemies. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] is the army of the land-locked Realm of Apex, defenders of the central region of the Tiers. Named for House Vendrien, the ruling dynasty of Apex, the Guard has a reputation for being as resilient and stubborn as the mountains themselves. Ostensibly beaten by [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' armies and forced to surrender in 429, the [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] resurfaced in 431, brazenly defying the Overlord's rule.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>[url=glossary:bleden mark]Bleden Mark[/url] is [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' knife in the shadows, the unseen drop of poison that enforces the Overlord's will. He reports to [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator, serving in his capacity as the final word to those who hold [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' law in contempt. 

Few know the origin of the Archon of Shadows, or how [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] maintains a hold on him. Those who anger the Archon never live long past sunset.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>[url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator is the Archon of Justice, ruler of the conquered realms, and arbiter of disputes. Oldest of the Archons sent to conquer the Tiers, [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] speaks with [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' authority. His true appearance remains hidden behind an iron mask - the Face of Judgment.

[url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] is an impartial, sober creature wholly obsessed with justice and order. Though assumed to be a powerful combatant, [url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] rarely strays from his throne room - entrusting his Court of Fatebinders to act as his eyes and ears - as well as judges, juries, and executioners.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>As tall as the hills, [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] is the Archon of Stone - master of earth and soil, destroyer of mountains and cities. [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url] is the reluctant leader of the Earthshaker Guild, though he is less their teacher and more their object of study. The massive Archon is sworn to [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url], and provides arcane support to the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] war effort.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>Sirin is the Archon of Song, and the youngest Archon sent to conquer the Tiers. Young and inexperienced, Sirin is sworn to [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url], who uses her powers of charm and manipulation to swell the ranks of the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url] with 'volunteers.'</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Built in the shadow of an Oldwalls junction in the realm of Haven, [url=glossary:lethian's crossing]Lethian's Crossing[/url] is a growing trading settlement. The nearby rivers are rich in iron ore, though the locals lack the technology to smelt and forge the element.

In the years following [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' conquest of the Tiers, the population of [url=glossary:lethian's crossing]Lethian's Crossing[/url] swelled with refugees fleeing the destruction of their homelands. The presence of the [url=glossary:forge-bound]Forge-Bound[/url] mining the iron, along with their guards, makes this makeshift settlement a vital resource for [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' armies.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Realms of Azure, Apex, Stalwart, and Haven are collectively known as the [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url], and together they represent the major political factions of the Tiers. For centuries, the [url=glossary:younger realms]Younger Realms[/url] have battled amongst themselves for control of the Tiers, with every realm having been at war with each other at some point in memorable history.

This lack of unified resistance allowed [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' armies to swiftly conquer the Tiers.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:blade grave]Blade Grave[/url] is the name given to what remains of the Realm of Stalwart, after its ruination when [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] proclaimed the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Storms upon the lands. The magical storms struck the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] and [url=glossary:unbroken]Unbroken[/url] armies during the height of their engagement, now most of what remains is a blighted landscape of discarded armor and weapons, and high winds of rust and human dust.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:stone sea]Stone Sea[/url] is the name given to what remains of the land of Azure after [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Stone devastated the landscape. Once a rolling landscape of winding rivers and fertile plains, tectonic shifts have altered the landscape - choking rivers, collapsing roads, and altering the landscape for hundreds of leagues.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>Named for its position between two realms (the Northern Empire and the Southern Tiers), the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url] (and its surrounding lands, known as the Bastard Tier) is a melting pot of cultures, and a place of commerce and intrigue.

The Tiersmen of the South view the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url] as a place of wealth and excess, but to the people of the Northern Empire, the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url] is little more than a sprawling slum.

[url=glossary:tunon]Tunon[/url] the Adjudicator established his Court in the [url=glossary:bastard city]Bastard City[/url]. From this foothold in the Tiers, he and his Court of Fatebinders impose [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' laws upon the conquered land.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>[url=glossary:ascension hall]Ascension Hall[/url] is the name of the inner sanctum of the old citadel built at the geographical center of [url=glossary:vendrien's well]Vendrien's Well[/url]. It was here that the [url=glossary:vendrien guard]Vendrien Guard[/url] signed the surrender of 429.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:crimson spears]Crimson Spears[/url] are the personal gang of [url=glossary:the voices of nerat]the Voices of Nerat[/url]. These top enforcers of the Chorus answer only to the Archon of Secrets and all gang members must follow their orders as if they were the words of the Archon of Secrets himself.

In contrast to the poorly equipped mobs they command, the [url=glossary:crimson spears]Crimson Spears[/url] are armed with fine bronze and rigorous training - and their skills are regularly tested by rivals for their status. In the [url=glossary:scarlet chorus]Scarlet Chorus[/url], even the top gang leaders must be ready to prove their strength if they wish to lead.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>The [url=glossary:iron guard]Iron Guard[/url] is the [url=glossary:disfavored]Disfavored[/url] high command, an inner circle of commanders hand-picked by [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url] for lifelong service, tactical brilliance, or true dedication to the craft of personal combat. The [url=glossary:iron guard]Iron Guard[/url] act as [url=glossary:graven ashe]Graven Ashe[/url]'s chief advisors when the Archon is present, and when he is absent, they speak with his direct authority.

Even the youngest [url=glossary:iron guard]Iron Guard[/url] has years of training and the finest iron the [url=glossary:forge-bound]Forge-Bound[/url] mage-smiths can create - making these elite commanders nearly unrivaled on the field of battle. These senior leaders are expected to lead from the front of the phalanx - it said that the [url=glossary:iron guard]Iron Guard[/url] fear only one thing: dying in their beds instead of in battle.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>The leader of a Beast tribe. A supremacy almost always held by a female, this rank is won and defended through vicious bloodshed and fights for dominance rather than birthright. Many Alphas may exist within a single tribe, but only one can rise above the others as [url=glossary:prima]Prima[/url].</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>A Beast who has either chosen to leave or otherwise been outcast from their tribe.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>The ranking second-in-command of a Beast tribe. A position often held by the most savage of Beastwomen, the [url=glossary:bolverk]Bolverk[/url]'s primary responsibility is to enforce order and obedience within the tribe and carry out the [url=glossary:prima]Prima[/url]'s commands. In the smaller structure of a pack, the [url=glossary:bolverk]Bolverk[/url] performs these same duties in loyalty to the Alpha.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>The largest spanning Beast tribe in the entirety of the Tiers, the [url=glossary:stonestalkers]Stonestalkers[/url] of Azure nearly tripled in population during a period of domestication and forced labor in service to the farmers and ranchers of the realm. However, like all Beasts, the [url=glossary:stonestalkers]Stonestalkers[/url] were born wild and yearned to range free, unfettered by humans within their own homeland.

In ancient times the tribe was known as the Meadowkins, but they were denied a name during their centuries of enslavement.

In the turmoil created by [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url]' invasion of the Tiers and conquest of Azure, the Beasts rebelled and won their freedom. Drawn to the enigmatic presence of [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url], Archon of Stone, the Beasts took the name '[url=glossary:stonestalker]Stonestalker[/url]' as their own.

After [url=glossary:cairn]Cairn[/url]'s defeat when [url=glossary:kyros]Kyros[/url] proclaimed the [url=glossary:edict]Edict[/url] of Stone on Azure - creating the [url=glossary:stone sea]Stone Sea[/url] - the [url=glossary:stonestalkers]Stonestalkers[/url] retreated into the wilds. The humans who have since encroached on their territory have been slaughtered.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>Archon</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
